headline: Insurance stocks, Levi's outlook, Super Micro pops: Market Minute
summary: Brad Smith outlines some of the top headlines investors need to know on Market Minute. Healthcare stocks like Humana (HUM), UnitedHealth (UNH), and CVS (CVS) rise after the US boosts Medicare reimbursement rates. Levi Strauss (LEVI) stock is in focus after the company maintained its full-year outlook and said it expects "minimal impact" from tariffs in the upcoming quarter. Super Micro Computer (SMCI) extends gains after being the top performer in the S&P 500 (^GSPC) during Monday's session. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.

headline: Where Will Super Micro Computer Stock Be in 1 Year?
summary: This scramble for AI dominance lets hardware providers like Super Micro Computer (NASDAQ: SMCI) leverage a picks-and-shovels business model to provide the data-center equipment other companies need to build and deploy consumer-facing large language models (LLMs).  Let's explore what the next 12 months might have in store for the company.  At the time of writing, Supermicro shares have fallen more than 70% from their all-time high of $118.82, reached in March 2024.
